snippet.textDisplay: Pearl Jam is one of, if not my all-time favorite band!!! Pearl Jam's self-titled album from 2006 was absolutely amazing and their last truly great album!!! 2009's Backspacer and 2013's Lightning Bolt were that just ok, not great types of albums. I happened to turn my car radio onto NJ station 95.9 the RAT a few days ago and it was playing towards the beginning of this song(at 1:25 mark) and I thought wow this is really awesome/interesting song with a really groovy bass guitar, then I heard the epic voice and thought to my self holy shit this is Eddie Vedder and Pearl Jam!!!! I didn't recognize this song and thought that this has to be new, so I immediately went online and saw that this is a new song called “Dance Of The Clairvoyants” and that Pear Jam is indeed coming out with a new album in early March of this year. I was so amped and excited, this is the best thing that I've heard from Pearl Jam in a very long time!!! I just hope to God that “Dance Of The Clairvoyants” isn't just a standout single and that the rest of this new album is really good as well!!!!
